0s, he showed that a properly graduated electric shock could restore the rhythm of a fibrillating heart — the experimental basis of modern cardiac defibrillation. Alone or with collaborators he published more than forty papers on the circulation."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"Edited the physiology journal thirty-two years, mostly unpaid","body":"He served as managing editor of the American Journal of Physiology for thirty-two years, much of it without pay. He made the journal self-supporting and in 1921 helped found its companion, Physiological Reviews."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"donald-hooker-1876"},"I01359":{"id":"I01359","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Edith","middle_name":"Houghton","last_name":"Hooker","maiden_name":"Houghton","married_names":["Hooker"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Edith Houghton Hooker","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780502587/edithhoughton_h0zpmb.png"},"birth":{"year":1879,"month":12,"day":29,"city":"Buffalo","county":"Erie","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1948,"month":10,"day":23,"city":"Baltimore","state":"Maryland","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":0,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["social_reform"],"notable_blurb":"Maryland suffrage leader and social reformer","primary_url":"https://msa.maryland.gov/msa/educ/exhibits/womenshallfame/html/hooker.html","primary_url_label":"Maryland Women's Hall of Fame"},"parents":{"father_name":"Alfred Augustus Houghton","mother_name":"Caroline Garlinghouse"},"number_of_marriages"